{:component/id :orbiplex/whisper
 :component/title "Orbiplex Whisper"
 :component/type :node-attached-module
 :component/status :done

 :summary
 "Node-attached social-signal exchange component for rumor intake, redaction,
 thresholding, and opt-in association bootstrap."

 :must-implement
 [{:cap/id :rumor-intake-and-publication
   :title "Rumor Intake and Publication"
   :kind :protocol
   :based-on ["doc/project/20-memos/orbiplex-whisper.md"
              "doc/project/30-stories/story-005-whisper-rumor-intake.md"
              "doc/project/40-proposals/013-whisper-social-signal-exchange.md"]
   :schemas ["whisper-signal.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Capture rumor-style input without flattening it into evidence"
    "Run bounded local redaction, paraphrase, and idiolect reduction"
    "Require user approval before publication"
    "Implement intake/redaction as a supervised Rust middleware package with its own operator UI surface"
    "Store raw user input and intermediate redaction drafts only in local/private Memarium state before public publication"
    "Allow the sanitizing step to be supplied by another configured middleware package without changing the downstream publishable `whisper-signal.v1` contract"
    "Emit `whisper-signal` artifacts with explicit epistemic class and routing/privacy intent"
    "Use `whisper-signal.v1` directly for the Agora M4 public/federated smoke, with nym-authored Agora envelope identity and inline-first nym proof"
    "Use Agora only for disclosure-safe public or federation-scoped signals"
    "Keep private-correlation and direct-only whisper bodies off public Agora topics"]
   :status :done}

  {:cap/id :interest-and-threshold-coordination
   :title "Interest and Threshold Coordination"
   :kind :protocol
   :based-on ["doc/project/20-memos/orbiplex-whisper.md"
              "doc/project/30-stories/story-005-whisper-rumor-intake.md"
              "doc/project/40-proposals/013-whisper-social-signal-exchange.md"]
   :schemas ["whisper-interest.v1"
             "whisper-threshold-reached.v1"
             "association-room-proposal.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Register local relevance without premature disclosure"
    "Recognize threshold crossings under policy, with Agora M4 proving the minimal rule: two distinct eligible nodes, same `topic/class`, same `signal/similarity-key`, bounded time window"
    "Derive deterministic bootstrap sets"
    "Publish association-room proposals as public/federated Agora records with redacted/bootstrap-only content"
    "Emit deterministic `whisper-threshold-reached.v1` and `association-room-proposal.v1` records as projection-authority-signed, issuer-scoped derived claims"
    "Prevent derived-record loops with deterministic ids, source-kind exclusion, and derivation refs"
    "Preserve opt-in enrollment and never auto-enroll humans"
    "Expose threshold/proposal state for the Story-005 three-node smoke"]
   :status :done}]

 :may-implement
 [{:cap/id :aggregate-topic-notices
   :title "Aggregate Topic Notices"
   :kind :optional
   :based-on ["doc/project/20-memos/orbiplex-whisper.md"
              "doc/project/40-proposals/013-whisper-social-signal-exchange.md"]
   :schemas ["whisper-threshold-reached.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Emit coarse aggregate notices after threshold crossing"
    "Keep aggregate discovery hints weaker than case disclosure"]
   :status :optional}]

 :out-of-scope
 ["Transport-layer anonymity and relay topology"
  "Automatic exposure of identities to one another"
  "Hard semantic duplicate suppression in v1"
  "Using Agora for private-correlation or direct-only whisper bodies"]

 :consumes
 ["whisper-signal.v1"
  "whisper-interest.v1"]

 :produces
 ["whisper-signal.v1"
  "whisper-interest.v1"
  "whisper-threshold-reached.v1"
  "association-room-proposal.v1"]

 :notes
 ["Whisper intake/redaction should be implemented as a supervised HTTP middleware service; shared transport-independent semantics belong in `whisper-core`."
  "Post-M4 productization adds a host-owned provider-policy shape for Inquirium/model-runtime redaction providers and a secretless simulator acceptance bridge without making adapters publication authorities."
  "`whisper-core` carries production-shaped source, routing, privacy, correlation, association-room, and public-gossip promotion contracts; concrete UI and relay runtime layers consume those contracts later."
  "Callers of outbound privacy should declare intent, not name a concrete relay module."
  "Agora M4 uses Story-005 as the three-node public/federated smoke: node A and node B submit similar sanitized signals, node C runs the Agora relay/server, and threshold/proposal state is rebuilt from accepted public records."]}
